Editor's note: The world economy is struggling with sluggish growth, amid a turbulent geopolitical situation, COVID-19 pandemic, serious disruptions to supply chains, and surging inflation rates. However, there are still bright spots in an increasingly uncertain world economic outlook. As the largest developing country with a population of more than 1.4 billion, China maintains positive economic growth over the past three years during the pandemic, while undertaking various risks and challenges, so as to gain the edge and embrace the future. China's development has attracted world media attention. What is their opinion and forecast of the Chinese economy? (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at opinions@cgtn.com. Follow @thouse_opinions on Twitter to discover the latest commentaries in the CGTN Opinion Section.)